@NODE Problems "Problems running Warhost"

If you experience any problems running Warhost, first try disabling things
such as screen blankers, which can often interfere badly with Amos programs.

If this still does not work, ensure that as few commodities and other
background utilities are running as possible.

If you STILL find problems then try disabling the CPU caches.  On 040 and
possibly 060 machines the caches are a MAJOR source of problems with
Warhost, due to a combination of poor coding (by Amos) and poor cache
implementation.  020 and 030 machines suffer less but may still cause
trouble on some accelerator boards.  On 030 systems, the Data Burst cache
should be set to off, which is the default.  If in doubt, type CPU at the
command prompt.

Finally, if you still can't get the thing to work, give me a call.  Maybe I
can help.

--

Wez

@ENDNODE

